{"name": "telepath", "metadata": {"name": "telepath", "version": "0.3.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Environment :: Web Environment", "Framework :: Django", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: BSD License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3 :: Only"], "home_page": "https://github.com/wagtail/telepath", "license": "BSD", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A library for exchanging data between Python and JavaScript", "upload_time": 1686571661}, "documentation": ["# telepath\n\n*telepath* is a Django library for exchanging data between Python and JavaScript, allowing you to build apps with rich client-side interfaces while keeping the business logic in server-side code.\n\n## What does it do?\n\nIt provides a mechanism for packing structured data, including Python objects, into a JSON-serializable format. This mechanism can be extended to support any Python class, by registering the class with a corresponding JavaScript implementation. The packed data can then be included in an HTTP response, and unpacked in JavaScript to obtain an equivalent data structure to the original. Think of it as [`pickle`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/pickle.html), but with the unpickling happening in the browser.\n\nFull documentation: https://wagtail.github.io/telepath/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "telepath.test_settings", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "telepath.test_settings.INSTALLED_APPS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.test_settings.SECRET_KEY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.test_settings.STATIC_URL", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "telepath", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "telepath.DICT_RESERVED_KEYS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.STRING_REF_MIN_LENGTH", "type": null, "documentation": ["do not turn strings shorter than this into references"]}, {"name": "telepath.registry", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.JSContext", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.register", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "telepath.UnpackableTypeError", "bases": ["TypeError"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.Node", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.Node.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.Node.emit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Intermediate representation of a packed value. Subclasses represent a particular value\ntype, and implement emit_verbose (returns a dict representation of a value that can have\nan _id attached) and emit_compact (returns a compact representation of the value, in any\nJSON-serialisable type).\n\nIf this node is assigned an id, emit() will return the verbose representation with the\nid attached on first call, and a reference on subsequent calls. To disable this behaviour\n(e.g. for small primitive values where the reference representation adds unwanted overhead),\nset self.use_id = False."]}, {"name": "telepath.ValueNode", "bases": ["Node"], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.ValueNode.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.ValueNode.emit_verbose", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "do