 arguments to be passed to the constructor\n- get_media(obj) or class Media: media definitions necessary for unpacking\n\nThe adapter should then be registered with register(adapter, cls)."]}, {"name": "telepath.AutoAdapter", "bases": ["Adapter"], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.AutoAdapter.pack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "context", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Adapter for objects that define their own telepath_pack method that we can simply delegate to."]}, {"name": "telepath.JSContextBase", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.JSContextBase.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.JSContextBase.base_media", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.JSContextBase.add_media", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "media", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "js", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "css", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.JSContextBase.pack", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Base class for JSContext classes obtained through AdapterRegistry.js_context_class.\nSubclasses of this are assigned the following class attributes:\nregistry - points to the associated AdapterRegistry\ntelepath_js_path - path to telepath.js (as per standard Django staticfiles conventions)\n\nA JSContext handles packing a set of values to be used in the same request; calls to\nJSContext.pack will return the packed representation and also update the JSContext's media\nproperty to include all JS needed to unpack the values seen so far."]}, {"name": "telepath.AdapterRegistry", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.AdapterRegistry.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "telepath_js_path", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.AdapterRegistry.register", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.AdapterRegistry.find_adapter", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.AdapterRegistry.js_context_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "telepath.AdapterRegistry.js_context_base_class", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Manages the mapping of Python types to their corresponding adapter implementations."]}, {"name": "telepath.ValueContext", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.ValueContext.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "parent_context", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.ValueContext.add_media", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.ValueContext.build_node", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "val", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "telepath.ValueContext._build_new_node", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A context instantiated for each top-level value that JSContext.pack is called on. Results from\nthis context's build_node method will be kept in a lookup table. If, over the course of\nbuilding the node tree for the top level value, we encounter multiple references to the same\nvalue, a reference to the existing node will be generated rather than building it again. Calls\nto add_media are passed back to the parent context so that multiple calls to pack() will have\ntheir media combined in a single bundle."]}], "exports": [{"name": "telepath.cached_property", "xref": {"fqname": "django.utils.functional.cached_property", "project": null}}, {"name": "telepath.forms", "xref": {"fqname": "django.forms", "project": null}}, {"name": "telepath.MediaDefiningClass", "xref": {"fqname": "django.forms.MediaDefiningClass", "project": null}}, {"name": "telepath.Promise", "xref": {"fqname": "django.utils.functional.Promise", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "telepath.tests", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "telepath.tests.Artist", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "telepath.tests.Artist.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "name", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}, {"name": "tel